Thrust and Power Loading¶

class design.wingpowerloading.WingPowerLoading(*args, **kwargs)[source]¶

This class will construct the wing and power loading plot for the fixed wing UAV based on the input MTOW. The requirements are the climb rate and climb gradient. There are assumed values for: C_lmax, Stall speed, propeller efficiency, zero-lift drag coefficient, Aspect Ratio and Oswald Efficiency Factor. All Values are in SI Units unless stated.

Parameters:
  • mtow (float) – The MTOW from class I
  • mission (str) – The UAV performance goal
  • range (float) – The UAV design range in km
  • endurance (float) – The UAV design endurance in hrs
  • pl_target_weight (float) – The UAV design payload weight in kg
  • handlaunch (bool) – Whether the user requires the UAV to be hand launched
  • maximum_lift_coefficient (list) – A list of three C_lmax’s that the wing is assumed to generate which create multiple lines on the thrust/wing loading plots.
  • AR (list) – A list of two potential aspect ratios for the design
  • eta_prop (float) – This is the assumed propeller efficiency.
  • eta_motor (float) – This is the assumed motor efficiency.
  • e_factor (float) – This is the assumed oswald efficiency factor.
  • rho (float) – This is the STD ISA sea level density
  • rho_cr (float) – This is the ISA Density at 3km height for the climb rate power loading equation.
  • zero_lift_drag (float) – This is the assumed Value of Zero-Lift Drag Coefficient.
  • climb_rate (float) – This is the assumption for Required Climb Rate in m/s, Same as Sparta UAV 1.1.2.
  • climb_gradient (float) – This is the assumed Climb Gradient to clear 10m object 17m away.
  • stall_speed (float) – This is the assumed stall speed for the UAV.

Below is the assumed Climb Gradient to clear 10m object 17m away.

climbcoefs[source]¶

An attribute which adds a safety factor to the lift coefficient in order to not stall out during climb-out. Modifying the lift coefficient changes drag coefficients as well due to induced drag the latter part of this code computes the new drag coefficients.

Returns:Dictionary containing modified lift coefficients (‘climb_lift’) and drag coefficients (‘climb_drag’)
cruise_parameters[source]¶

This attribute calculates the cruise parameters related to the requirement on range [km], or endurance [h]. These relations are from the year 1 Intro to aeronautics flight mechanics module.

Returns:Required battery capacity due to plane drag.
Return type:dict
designpoint[source]¶

An attribute which adds a safety factor to the lift coefficient in order to not stall out during climb-out. Modifying the lift coefficient changes drag coefficients as well due to induced drag, the latter part of this code computes the new drag coefficients.

Returns:Dictionary containing design_point variables (‘lift_coefficient’) and drag coefficients (‘climb_drag’)
Return type:dict

stall_speed[source]¶

This attribute calculates the stall speed for the UAV depending on whether it will be hand launched or not. If hand launched, the stall speed is to be 8 m/s and if not, it is 12 m/s.

Return type:float
wingloading[source]¶

This attribute calculates the 3 required wing loadings from the lift equation, using the stall speed and the three assumed C_lmax’s. If the UAV is to be hand launched, a lower stall speed is used. At this moment, this is the only requirement on the wing loading.

Returns:Required wing loading for 3 different C_lmax’s
Return type:dict

This is a dummy list of wing loadings for iterating in the Power Loading Equations.

Returns:List of wing loadings
Return type:List
